request.description:
## Generate Webhook Secret

> 🚧 **PLACEHOLDER** — Confirm the exact endpoint path with Vesicash backend. The request structure and response shape below follow standard API patterns.

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/webhooks/secret`

Generates (or rotates) a webhook signing secret for your account. Store this secret securely on your server — you will use it to verify the HMAC-SHA256 signature on every incoming Vesicash webhook payload.

---

### Request Body

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `webhook_url` | string | ✅ | Your server endpoint that will receive webhook events |

---

### Response

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "code": 201,
  "data": {
    "webhook_secret": "whsec_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX",
    "webhook_url": "https://yourserver.com/webhooks/vesicash"
  }
}
```

---

### How to verify a webhook payload

```javascript
const crypto = require('crypto');

function verifyWebhook(rawBody, signature, secret) {
  const expected = crypto
    .createHmac('sha256', secret)
    .update(rawBody)
    .digest('hex');
  return crypto.timingSafeEqual(
    Buffer.from(expected),
    Buffer.from(signature)
  );
}

// In your Express handler:
app.post('/webhooks/vesicash', express.raw({ type: '*/*' }), (req, res) => {
  const sig = req.headers['x-vesicash-signature'];
  if (!verifyWebhook(req.body, sig, process.env.WEBHOOK_SECRET)) {
    return res.status(400).send('Invalid signature');
  }
  const event = JSON.parse(req.body);
  // Handle event...
  res.json({ received: true });
});
```

---

> ⚠️ **Security:** Calling this endpoint again will rotate your secret. Update your server's stored secret immediately — old signatures will fail.
